  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (f05fdd8 2023-04-27T00:04:10.201981651Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\n`changePrank` with no prank started used to work and was properly changing prank before enforcing it in https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/4827 (https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/commit/8973b2b3ef1873ea1f81fdeb4dbbaa35a5881163)\r\nFor backwards compatibility reasons, can we have the `changePrank` exempted from this new check? (test works OK if `foundryup -v nightly-dedc31eed0683764ae542b9b575c21f6bd2a5c60`)\r\n\r\n```Solidity\r\npragma solidity 0.8.14;\r\n\r\nimport '@std/Test.sol';\r\nimport '@std/Vm.sol';\r\n\r\ncontract SampleTest is Test {\r\n\r\n    address bob;\r\n    address alice;\r\n\r\n    function setUp() external {\r\n        bob = makeAddr(\"bob\");\r\n        alice = makeAddr(\"alice\");\r\n\r\n        vm.prank(bob);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function test_sample() external {\r\n        changePrank(alice);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nRunning 1 test for tests/forge/SampleTest.t.sol:SampleTest\r\n[FAIL. Reason: No prank in progress to stop] test_sample() (gas: 5191)\r\nTest result: FAILED. 0 passed; 1 failed; finished in 613.35Âµs\r\n```",
